VERDICT: APPROVED_WITH_COMMENTS

The implementation is functionally sound and can be accepted, but it includes minor non-blocking scope/maintainability issues.

Critical findings / analysis:
- The project is set up and runnable via `.replit` workflow (`python3 -m http.server 5000` on port 5000), and the UI/theme conversion work is consistently applied across HTML/CSS/JS.
- The girlfriend-to-friend adaptation is coherently implemented: blue-forward palette, updated copy, friendship-oriented letter text, game icons switched to `gamepad/balloon`, and fireworks palette updated.
- Countdown and birthday card were updated to July 6; JS parses and runs cleanly (`node --check` passes), and icon IDs used by the game are present in `index.html`.
- Non-blocking concern: the countdown is hardcoded to a specific year (`new Date(2026, 6, 6, ...)`). After this date window, behavior will no longer represent a future birthday unless manually updated.
- Non-blocking concern: some personalization values are still placeholders (`Best Friend`, generic friendship start date in code comments), which is acceptable for setup but should be completed in follow-up tasks.

Security:
- None observed.

Next actions:
1. Parameterize or compute the next upcoming birthday year dynamically to avoid annual manual edits.
2. Complete remaining personalization tasks (real friend name/photo, actual friendship start date, final custom letter) before declaring the full feature set done.
3. Keep `replit.md` guidance synchronized with actual editable fields as those follow-up tasks are completed.

